HEADWORD: Melocotoon
<hw>Mel`o*co*toon"</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp. <ets>melocoton</ets> a kind of
peach tree and its fruit, L. <ets>malum cotonium</ets>, or
<ets>cotonea</ets>, or <ets>Cydonia</ets>, a quince, or quince tree,
lit., apple of <ets>Cydonia</ets>, Gr. <?/ <?/. See
<er>Quince</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A
quince.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A kind of peach having one side deep
red, and the flesh yellow.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>malacatoon</asp>, <asp>malacotune</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
